from his body, leaving him in the white, skin tight undergarment. He walked to a table in the spaceous main courtyard and sat down.<br>
<br>
A sigh escaped him. It had been such an exhausting day. He moved the hair from his eyes. He kicked off the metal shoes, they clanked as the hit the ground. He admired his cute toes, and wiggled them a bit. He smiled. He removed his gaunlets, one by one, tossing them to the ground. And then constricting lower-body armor.<br>
<br>
Ah, sweet freedom. Apollo began to glow and flashed into a nice comfertable beige tunic. He placed his laurel crown upon his head and didn't even bother to put on sandels. He was home, no need to be show-offish. He got up and wandered over to where Aphrodite was sitting, near the reflecting pool. He stopped and gazed at her. He had known her for so long, she had been his most trusted confidante and truest friend. Limping over to a lounge sofa he laid upon it sighing loudly.<br>
<br>
He moved, trying to get comfertable, but hissed in pain as he hit a tender spot.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ugh. This is gunna be an annoying interference I bet.&quot; he smiled to Aphrodite, who looked slightly troubled. He knew very well she didn't want this war to continue. But it had to. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/DPratt1000/YH/apollo.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 11/23/01 11:36:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 402<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/23/01 11:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=193>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> War-Dawn vs Fogstone.</span><hr size=1>  Thank whoever taught Dawn a good war stance, with a dagger and a sword. Once the five knives had been thrown at her, the movement of metal against metal, blocked all but one of the blades launched at her. Now.. Dawn wouldn't be stupid enough to just let it launch past her, and hit into her flesh. <br>
