&quot;I do not know Dite.&quot; he shook his head.<br>
<br>
&quot;The ego of man is so strong. But the will of Zeus is stronger than all man's ego put together. But as usual he sits on the fence. Refusing to take sides. He says its because he's unbiased. I say its because he is a coward.&quot;<br>
<br>
Apollo's eyes darkened as he spoke of his father. There was something about that man that he resented, and he was bound to find out what is was and try to resolve it. He didn't like not enjoying the presence of his father. He was supposed to revel in it, instead he despised it.<br>
<br>
&quot;This will come to an end soon. I promise.&quot; and that was all he said, with a smile. He couldn't say anymore. All he could do was promise it would end. And it would...in time. <p>      *~*The Golden God*~*
